31:38.566 --> 31:41.569
- You fell?
- I fell, Mark.

31:51.378 --> 31:53.180
Wait, your friends
just up and bailed on you?

31:54.582 --> 31:55.983
I guess.

31:57.217 --> 31:59.351
Probably didn't know what to do

31:59.353 --> 32:00.487
and booked it.

32:01.656 --> 32:03.323
Why the fuck didn't you call me?

32:04.425 --> 32:07.125
Because I smashed my phone.

32:07.127 --> 32:08.226
Well, that's fucking great.

32:08.228 --> 32:09.697
Please don't tell Mom.

32:18.005 --> 32:19.707
Hey, do I need to take you
to the hospital?

32:21.074 --> 32:24.044
Mmm-mmm. I just need to rest.

32:25.647 --> 32:27.247
You wanna take my bed?

32:27.782 --> 32:30.716
No, I'm just

32:30.718 --> 32:33.353
gonna pass out right here,
if that's all right.

32:36.558 --> 32:38.524
Could you close
the blinds though?

32:38.526 --> 32:40.060
It's fucking bright in here.

32:41.763 --> 32:43.665
Hey, you gotta do me
a favor, though.

32:44.298 --> 32:46.064
Call Mom.

32:46.066 --> 32:48.202
Tell her you dropped your phone
in the toilet or something.

32:49.169 --> 32:50.971
- Okay?
- Mmm-hmm.

33:25.439 --> 33:27.709
- What time is it?
- 7:00.

33:28.308 --> 33:29.376
Oh.

33:30.244 --> 33:32.580
It feels like
I've been asleep forever.

33:33.380 --> 33:34.582
It's Sunday.

33:36.483 --> 33:37.619
Holy shit.

33:39.721 --> 33:41.288
You hungry?

33:42.824 --> 33:45.156
Not really.

33:45.158 --> 33:46.794
You should
eat something anyway.

33:58.372 --> 34:00.773
You know what? I'm okay.

34:00.775 --> 34:02.276
Just eat it.

34:19.793 --> 34:22.262
Whoa! Hey!

34:28.636 --> 34:31.103
Lolo, you okay in there?

34:34.876 --> 34:36.376
What's going on with you?

34:37.911 --> 34:39.512
Jesus.

34:39.514 --> 34:41.813
You sure you don't need
to go to the hospital?

34:41.815 --> 34:44.686
No. I'm fine.

34:46.286 --> 34:48.155
- Laurel.
- I'm fine!

35:00.902 --> 35:02.202
Okay.

35:18.720 --> 35:20.420
Ah.

36:48.275 --> 36:49.476
Fuck.

36:53.848 --> 36:55.848
Hi, can I help you guys
with something?

36:55.850 --> 36:57.550
Is Laurel home?

36:57.552 --> 36:59.051
It's a bit late.

36:59.053 --> 37:00.420
Is it?

37:04.759 --> 37:06.794
Are you gonna
let us in or what?

37:07.995 --> 37:09.429
Yeah, sure.

37:11.632 --> 37:12.633
Hey, kid.

37:14.769 --> 37:17.004
- Nice boxers.
- Yeah, thanks.

37:20.641 --> 37:21.909
How are you feeling?

37:23.878 --> 37:25.578
I'm fine.

37:25.580 --> 37:27.515
You were supposed to
meet us, remember?

37:28.816 --> 37:31.382
Yeah, sorry about that.

37:31.384 --> 37:32.885
Sorry about the other night.

37:32.887 --> 37:34.053
I'm glad you're okay.

37:34.055 --> 37:35.554
Whoa, whoa, wait.

37:35.556 --> 37:37.792
Are these the fucking assholes
who ditched you?

37:42.964 --> 37:44.832
No, they're not.

37:46.399 --> 37:48.768
Thought we'd stop by
and see if you're still down.

37:48.770 --> 37:51.637
Glad we found the place.
You weren't answering your phone.

37:51.639 --> 37:54.405
Okay, why's everyone
talking so cryptically?

37:54.407 --> 37:56.677
And why's she sorry
about the other night?

37:57.712 --> 38:00.012
Mark, can you just...

38:00.014 --> 38:01.580
Can you just go
put on some pants?

38:01.582 --> 38:02.984
He's fine the way he is.

38:03.951 --> 38:05.718
Oh, how fucking rude of me

38:05.720 --> 38:07.485
to be in my living room
in boxers

38:07.487 --> 38:09.755
at, the middle
of the fucking night?

38:09.757 --> 38:11.291
Mark!

38:15.930 --> 38:17.064
Okay.

38:20.067 --> 38:22.902
Yeah, just, um...

38:22.904 --> 38:24.605
Just give me a second
to get ready.

38:24.939 --> 38:26.007
Okay.

38:37.518 --> 38:39.685
- So, are you guys like...
- Vampires?

38:39.687 --> 38:40.755
Yup.

38:43.958 --> 38:45.858
Am I a vampire now?

38:45.860 --> 38:47.726
Do you wanna be?

38:47.728 --> 38:48.930
I don't know.

38:51.098 --> 38:53.032
Can vampires get drunk?

38:53.034 --> 38:55.102
Bitch, you can get
as lit as you want.

39:02.442 --> 39:03.878
Were you gonna kill me?

39:06.413 --> 39:07.615
Does that scare you?

39:08.583 --> 39:09.784
Not really.

39:10.585 --> 39:11.586
Why not?

39:14.487 --> 39:16.858
My life's already kind of
been like a horror movie.

39:17.892 --> 39:19.861
Most of it. So...

39:23.064 --> 39:24.532
Fuck it.

39:47.755 --> 39:50.591
Careful, that's the last one.

39:52.026 --> 39:53.192
What is it?

39:53.194 --> 39:54.727
The cure.

39:54.729 --> 39:55.995
If you take it
before you feed,

39:55.997 --> 39:57.632
you'll turn back
into your old self.

40:00.668 --> 40:02.637
Now would be the time
for any questions.

40:03.938 --> 40:05.571
Do you guys kill people?

40:05.573 --> 40:06.607
Indiscriminately.

40:07.842 --> 40:09.143
Innocent people?

40:10.044 --> 40:12.077
Say it's like 80/20.

40:12.079 --> 40:14.513
You know, we try
to target the trolls,

40:14.515 --> 40:16.916
the privileged and their
apathetic trust fund kids,

40:16.918 --> 40:20.152
but we're not a movement.

40:20.154 --> 40:21.956
We're a terrorist
organization, at best.

40:24.025 --> 40:25.760
So, you were gonna kill me.

40:26.694 --> 40:27.862
Yes.

40:29.196 --> 40:31.030
Why?

40:31.032 --> 40:33.100
People you're attracted to
taste better.

40:35.169 --> 40:36.804
I don't wanna kill people.

40:37.605 --> 40:38.804
Too bad.

40:38.806 --> 40:40.207
Knock it off.

40:42.877 --> 40:45.177
The world's a meatgrinder, kid.

40:45.179 --> 40:46.679
Especially if you're a woman.

40:46.681 --> 40:49.848
I don't think you need a Power Point
presentation to know that one's true.

40:49.850 --> 40:53.919
We're politically, socially,
and mythologically fucked.

40:53.921 --> 40:56.021
Our roles are secondary.

40:56.023 --> 41:00.059
Our body's suspect,
alien, other.

41:00.061 --> 41:03.862
We're made to be monsters,
so let's be monsters.

41:03.864 --> 41:06.065
Let's be gods.

41:06.067 --> 41:09.902
What we offer here is not
the chance to join a group,

41:09.904 --> 41:12.472
but the chance to
truly be an individual.

41:15.643 --> 41:17.078
That's the pitch.

41:23.617 --> 41:24.817
What about my family?

41:24.819 --> 41:26.151
What about them?

41:26.153 --> 41:28.456
Izzy directs music videos and
visits her brother all the time.

41:30.124 --> 41:32.992
Frog does tattoos out of her
dad's shop in Eagle Rock.

41:32.994 --> 41:34.061
And Roya...

41:34.829 --> 41:35.894
has a cat.

41:35.896 --> 41:37.763
Mister Kitty.

41:37.765 --> 41:39.499
We stick together
because we want to.

41:40.167 --> 41:42.001
Because it's safer.

41:42.003 --> 41:43.702
But you can do
whatever you want,

41:43.704 --> 41:45.804
just don't break the rules.

41:45.806 --> 41:47.606
All right, what are the rules?

41:47.608 --> 41:48.907
Glad you asked.

41:48.909 --> 41:50.209
The first rule of Bite Club...

41:50.211 --> 41:51.577
Bite Club?

41:51.579 --> 41:52.913
Juggalos was taken.

41:53.881 --> 41:55.247
We don't actually have a name.

41:55.249 --> 41:57.149
I just... I was trying
to sound cool.

41:57.151 --> 41:58.250
What about Bit Girls?

41:58.252 --> 42:00.319
Nah, sounds like we're
part of STEM or something.

42:00.321 --> 42:01.822
Anyway...

42:03.057 --> 42:05.124
Rule number one,

42:05.126 --> 42:07.760
you never glamour
another vampire.

42:07.762 --> 42:09.361
Okay? You never
invade their minds

42:09.363 --> 42:10.598
to affect their decisions.

42:12.700 --> 42:13.901
Rule number two.

42:14.835 --> 42:15.903
You kill what you eat.

42:16.871 --> 42:18.037
Otherwise it turns,

42:18.039 --> 42:20.606
and we're not ready for
that kind of expansion yet.

42:20.608 --> 42:22.975
All potential recruits are decided by
me, and me alone,

42:22.977 --> 42:24.278
but we all have veto power.

42:26.213 --> 42:30.017
Which brings me to our final,
and most important rule.

42:31.919 --> 42:34.021
You never, ever, turn a man.

42:35.056 --> 42:36.323
It's off limits.

42:37.191 --> 42:39.391
Men can't handle power.

42:39.393 --> 42:41.695
They have it already and look
at what they've done with it.

42:44.732 --> 42:45.833
What about me?

42:47.935 --> 42:49.737
Never crossed my mind.

42:56.377 --> 42:58.911
So, what do you say, ladies?

42:58.913 --> 43:01.816
All those in favor of Laurel
joining the V-Squad.

43:02.817 --> 43:03.884
Yup.

43:04.251 --> 43:05.252
Yeah.

43:08.789 --> 43:09.924
All right.

43:11.392 --> 43:12.660
K.

43:34.782 --> 43:38.050
This is Jacob.

43:38.052 --> 43:39.885
When Jacob isn't listening
to Joe Rogan

43:39.887 --> 43:42.955
prat along about ayahuasca,
he's on Twitter

43:42.957 --> 43:45.224
under the user name,
shitlordshaman89

43:45.226 --> 43:46.358
where he tells young women

43:46.360 --> 43:48.827
they deserve to be
raped to death.

43:48.829 --> 43:51.296
He also spends his time
growing conspiracy molds

43:51.298 --> 43:54.233
about the deep state and the
vile petri dish of subreddits

43:54.235 --> 43:56.168
with other
like-minded fucksticks.

43:56.170 --> 43:58.904
However,
one of these conspiracies

43:58.906 --> 44:01.273
involves the idea
that there's a secret cabal

44:01.275 --> 44:04.309
of female vampires
that stalk Los Angeles.

44:04.311 --> 44:06.347
Broken clocks, am I right?

44:07.381 --> 44:09.748
So, Jacob and his buddies,

44:09.750 --> 44:11.183
they get together
and they share stories

44:11.185 --> 44:13.018
and they fancy themselves
vampire hunters.

44:13.020 --> 44:15.053
Don't you, Jacob?

44:15.055 --> 44:16.390
Don't you, Jacob?

44:18.425 --> 44:21.793
Luckily for us,
Jacob is also on Tinder

44:21.795 --> 44:24.429
where he goes by his full
name, Jacob Oflinger,

44:24.431 --> 44:26.832
and, yes, he's posing
with a fish he caught.

44:26.834 --> 44:31.504
He describes himself as
old-fashioned and a bit fashy.

44:31.506 --> 44:33.939
All it took Frog was a few
choice photos to lure him out

44:33.941 --> 44:35.409
of whatever baby cave
he was holed up in.

44:40.247 --> 44:42.247
Crunch time, kid.

44:42.249 --> 44:43.982
This is the part
where you take the red pill

44:43.984 --> 44:45.350
and kick it in wonderland,

44:45.352 --> 44:47.388
or go back home to Kansas.

45:00.100 --> 45:01.168
That's it.

45:04.371 --> 45:06.373
You're nothing but a cat
with its prey.

45:15.382 --> 45:16.383
Do it!

45:19.554 --> 45:21.755
I'm sorry. I can't.

45:22.256 --> 45:23.390
I can't do it.

45:26.460 --> 45:28.160
No. You just need more time.

45:28.162 --> 45:30.028
Duke, what are you doing?
Let go of me.

45:30.030 --> 45:31.332
- Duke!
- Let go!

45:32.933 --> 45:35.000
- She's made up her mind.
- I know what I'm doing.

45:35.002 --> 45:36.868
Let me go! Help!

45:36.870 --> 45:40.272
- Let her go.
- Help me! Help!

45:40.274 --> 45:41.909
Help!

45:49.350 --> 45:50.550
What do we do now?

45:50.552 --> 45:52.417
- Nothing.
- What?

45:52.419 --> 45:53.954
We let her go.

45:54.556 --> 45:56.991
She'll learn. She'll feed.

45:58.959 --> 46:00.227
As for you...

46:18.212 --> 46:19.378
What's so fucking funny?

46:19.380 --> 46:21.081
We got you bitches in hell.

47:23.444 --> 47:25.143
What are you doing, man?
